        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 7:30PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Glenwood, or near Goshen, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tarentum, Hamilton Crossroads, Springhill, Mossy Grove, Antioch, Troy
University, Goshen, Henderson, Troy, and Brundidge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
